shopNotes: This BMW M3 arrived in our garage completely stock with only 35,000 miles on the engine. Originally the M3 came with a 3.0-liter twin-turbocharged inline 6, rated at 425 hp and 406 lb-ft of torque. But after improvements and tuning we increased the power to 536 hp and 480 lb-ft of torque. Our design crew also went through and added front and rear bumper diffusers, a rear spoiler to keep the rear wheels planted, and a bigger wheel package. This M3 now has a 0 to 60 time of 3.2 seconds and is ready for the next track day.

This 2013 Subaru WRX limited has been well taken care of and is a one-owner vehicle. It has low miles on the engine and is mostly stock with only tuning software installed and intake and exhaust improvements. Powered by a turbocharged 2.5L four-cylinder boxer engine that generates 315 horsepower and 298 lb/ft of torque. Our pros were able to launch this vehicle from 0-60 in 4.5 seconds while running a quarter-mile in 13.3 seconds. Our technicians have performed a full inspection of all components and dyno-tested the engine to verify the power and reliability of the vehicle.
